headline: This Winning Fund Pro Likes J&J, Lowe’s, and Utility Stocks
summary: Susan Bao’s large-cap JPMorgan fund has outperformed the S&P 500 over many years. She’s bullish on stocks, focused on bargains.

headline: Sherwin-Williams Stock Slips. Earnings Paint a Grim Picture of Customer Spending.
summary: Sherwin-Williams  presented a sobering picture of the state of consumer spending as the paint-and-coatings brand posted earnings for the fourth quarter.  Sherwin-Williams surpassed forecasts for both its top and bottom line.  Adjusted earnings came to $2.23 a share, surpassing the $2.04 consensus among analysts polled by FactSet.

headline: 3 Reasons to Sell LOW and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Over the past six months, Lowe's has been a great trade, beating the S&P 500 by 7.3%. Its stock price has climbed to $268.65, representing a healthy 16.8% increase. This run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
